            . On the 3d of February, between six and seven o'clock in the evening, I was in High-street, St. Giles's, I noticed the prisoner and another person following me for sometime; just as I crossed <placeName id="t18190217-129-crimeloc756">Denmark-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18190217-129-crimeloc756" type="placeName" value="Denmark-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18190217-129-crimeloc756" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190217-129-off754 t18190217-129-crimeloc756"></join> a person said,</p>
               <p>"the man has taken something out of your pocket." I immediately ran and collared the prisoner, who was pointed out to me - I saw the handkerchief in his hand; he threw it down, and said he had not got it.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
